s:860:"<p>A SCORM package is a collection of files which are packaged according to an agreed standard for learning objects. The SCORM activity module enables SCORM or AICC packages to be uploaded as a zip file and added to a course.</p>

<p>Content is usually displayed over several pages, with navigation between the pages. There are various options for displaying content in a pop-up window, with a table of contents, with navigation buttons etc. SCORM activities generally include questions, with grades being recorded in the gradebook.</p>

<p>SCORM activities may be used</p>

<ul>
<li>For presenting multimedia content and animations</li>
<li>As an assessment tool</li>
</ul>

